Westchester Municipalities

The municipality with the most new cases per capita in the past 14 days is Mount Kisco, where there have been 152 cases reported in the last two weeks (1,395 per 100,000 residents). Elmsford is also a recent hot spot, with 47 cases reported in the last two weeks (1,089 per 100,000).

Throughout the pandemic, the municipalities that have had the largest share of their population test positive for coronavirus are Elmsford (1 in 13) and Port Chester (1 in 13). The municipalities that have had the least cases per capita are Pound Ridge (1 in 60) and New Castle (1 in 41).
